He means the world to both of us and she let me have him. I asked her to let me keep him because really he‚Äôs the only thing that keeps me close to her and he‚Äôs what gives me hope that she‚Äôll come back... she told me she still loves me and she still has feelings.. she says she wants to come back but something is holding her back.. and I think it‚Äôs her ex.. come to find out when she left she started talking to him again... and she told him her feelings never faded from him.. I confronted her about it and now she ( wants time to herself ) and she‚Äôs not making a decision till she‚Äôs ready.. and right now listening to this song just reminds of the night we took a drive out.. singing this together and looking at eachother and just admiring eachother.. guys I really do love this girl.. throughout the time I‚Äôve known this girl I‚Äôm really happy to say I found the one.. she‚Äôs my key to happiness.. Had a girlfriend about 3 days ago who broke up with me for personal reason that i wont discuss for her own privacy. We were together for about 9 months and theres no amount of words i can put together in a sentence that can describe how much i loved this girl. As far as i can remember, this is one of the first songs that she sent to me that was a love song. It felt like she was personally asking me to never let her go, which I never ever wanted to do. I decided to learn it on my guitar and play it back for her as she sung the lyrics. Now that we are apart, i frequently come back to this song and remeber not only those times, but the entire 9 amazing months we were together. I never thought a song that could make me feel so special to her could now damn near bring me to tears listening to it, but i guess thats a bit of a cliche to say huh?
